About the Role

We are seeking a Security Engineer to help design, implement, and operate security controls across hybrid on-prem and cloud environments. This role focuses on network security, Zero Trust principles, automation, and incident response, working closely with infrastructure, cloud, and security operations teams.

The ideal candidate is hands-on, comfortable with modern security tooling, and able to translate security requirements into scalable technical solutions.

Key Responsibilities

Design, implement, and maintain network security controls, including next-generation firewalls, segmentation, and secure access patterns

Support Zero Trust initiatives, helping modernize remote access and identity-centric security architectures

Partner with Security Operations to support incident response, including triage, investigation, and containment activities

Develop and maintain automation and infrastructure-as-code to standardize security configurations and reduce manual effort

Implement and maintain centralized logging and monitoring to improve visibility across cloud and on-prem systems

Collaborate with cross-functional teams to align security controls with organizational standards and risk management goals

Contribute to security architecture reviews, proofs-of-concept, and continuous improvement initiatives

